<h2>
<a href="proximity-taxes">Proximity &amp; Taxes</a>
</h2>
</div>
</header>
<div class='post-body' id='post_body_123313'>
<p>It is amazing how important proximity to resources really is.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><span>A new enterprise, meanwhile, would be facing a choice between China, with a 15 percent corporate tax rate, proximity to all kinds of suppliers, and low costs, and the U.S., with a 35 percent tax rate (plus any state corporate income tax) and an ocean separating it from most component vendors.</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p><span><a href="http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/philg/2012/06/09/you-cant-engineer-around-tax-rates/">http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/philg/2012/06/09/you-cant-engineer-around-tax-ra...</a></span></p>
</div>

